This is part two of two of the Sacred Books of the East translation of
the Grihya Sutras. The Grihya Sutras are Vedic-era Hindu texts which
define rituals and laws relating to birth, initiation, marriage, and
death. This volume includes a synoptic comparison of each version, as
well as Max Müllers' translation of Apastamba's Yagna-Paribhasha-Sutras
and commentary, which features a special index.

